<title>USA: Tridex Corp Q1 net falls.</title>
<headline>Tridex Corp Q1 net falls.</headline>
<dateline>WESTPORT, Conn. 1997-04-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months ended</p>
<p>						    Mar 31,	 Mar 30,</p>
<p>							1997	    1996</p>
<p> Net sales				  $ 9,392,000   $ 7,752,000</p>
<p> Operating income (loss)		  (582,000)	 334,000</p>
<p> (Loss), continuing operations	  (235,000)	(69,000)</p>
<p> Income, discontinued operations	  873,000	 865,000</p>
<p> Net income				     638,000	 796,000</p>
<p>Earnings (loss) per common and</p>
<p>common-equivalent share:</p>
<p>  Continuing operations			 (.05)	   (.02)</p>
<p>  Discontinued operations			 .18	     .22</p>
<p>  Net income					  .13	     .20</p>
<p>Average common and equivalent</p>
<p>  shares outstanding			4,822,000     3,938,000</p>
<p>NOTE: The company said first quarter 1997 results include a one-time, non-cash charge of $404,000, or $0.18 per share, related to a stock incentive compensation agreement with its subsidiary, Ultimate Technology Corp.</p>
<p>The company also said per-share results for the current first quarter reflect a 22 percent increase in outstanding shares resulting from the exercise of options and warrants and the conversion of outstanding convertible debt to shares.</p>
